          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1639415347151-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potato is cooking, chop your<strong> creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>peanut butter</strong> in 350ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [475ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> nutty coconut stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pan with the <strong>nutty</strong> <strong>coconut stock</strong> and 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span>[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>,<strong> </strong>mix everything together and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1639415350596-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1639415350596-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1639415350596-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1639415350596-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1639415350596-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the pan, give everything a good mix up and cook, covered, for 10 min or until the sweet potato has softened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1639415352642-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1639415352642-x400.jpg",
